author: sfgate.com
title: Horoscope for Tuesday, 10/20/15 by Christopher Renstrom
text:
ARIES. (March 20 - April 19): Start out small when changing your daily regimen. It's minor adjustments, not willpower, that produce the most lasting results.
TAURUS. (April 20 - May 20): You're asked to make a personal sacrifice for the greater good, but hold off a bit before answering. You could still discover a way around this.
GEMINI. (May 21 - June 20): You don't like to play the fuddy-duddy because you're a child at heart, but considering the lack of supervision today, it looks like you're the designated adult.
CANCER. (June 21 - July 21): You tend to avoid confrontations, but dig in your heels and stand your ground. You can take the heat â€“ especially when it's only temporary.
LEO. (July 22 - Aug. 22): You can't be everyone's favorite, but you can choose the person whose opinion matters most and ditch the rest.
VIRGO. (Aug. 23 - Sept. 22): You've always supported people in pursuing their dreams and now they want to return the favor. Don't be shy about taking them up on it.
LIBRA. (Sept. 23 - Oct. 22): Suspend judgment until this weekend when you discover the real reason why someone acted the way s/he did. It will explain a lot of things.
SCORPIO. (Oct. 23 - Nov. 21): Be open to others' input. They may not have all the answers, but sometimes the right question is all you need to unlock a mental block.
SAGITTARIUS. (Nov. 22 - Dec. 20): Apply strong medicine to ailing finances. It's a bitter pill to swallow but a difficult cure promises the best result.
CAPRICORN. (Dec. 21 - Jan. 19): There are hints of change in your love life. People see you as their Rock of Gibraltar, but someone new sees you in a sexier light.
AQUARIUS. (Jan. 20 - Feb. 17): Don't rest on your laurels because your competition is counting on you to slow down after your recent victories. Keep pushing to the 27th.
PISCES. (Feb. 18 - March 19): The secret to getting people to lend a hand is coordinating timetables. The clearer you are about what you need (and when), the faster they deliver.
